<paragraph blockId="126.[189,1399,636,810]" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">
Species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thuy &amp; Meyer" authorityYear="2013" box="[325,493,673,699]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Alternacantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[325,493,673,699]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">Alternacantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with large LAPs displaying a pointed to tongue-shaped, relatively narrow dorsal edge; outer surface with a well-developed vertical striation; up to four moderately well-developed spurs on the outer proximal and inner distal edges; up to five spine articulations; distal edge of ventral arm plates evenly convex; distal edge of dorsal arm plates parabolic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
